# module: eng.workflow
# status: native_preview
# purpose: static and runtime workflow graph artifacts, run locks, rerun decisions, and workflow node status.
#
# Current implementation:
#   top-level workflow execution emits static_run_plan.json, run_plan.json,
#   run_lock.json, output_manifest.json, and run_log.json. The review document
#   links workflow graph metadata back to the RunPlan artifact, and IDE/VS Code
#   tooling can open the generated workflow artifacts directly.
#
# Planned helper vocabulary:
#   workflow stage
#   depends on
#   rerun if changed
#   workflow lock compare
#
# Review contract:
#   source hash, execution profile, graph nodes/edges, node status, artifact
#   hashes, input hash, rerun decision, and source spans.
#
# Non-goal:
#   this module does not introduce a separate DAG language yet. Current
#   workflow graphs are derived from executable top-level EngLang programs.
